<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.graphics.IStateGroupNode.SetPolygonCullMode" Title="SetPolygonCullMode method" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IStateGroupNode">IStateGroupNode</PageRef> ->
    SetPolygonCullMode
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>SetPolygonCullMode</TypeRef> method sets the <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IStateGroupNode.PolygonCullMode">PolygonCullMode</PageRef>
      for the <TypeRef>IStateGroupNode</TypeRef>. All child renderable nodes will have their polygons culled according
      to this mode. It is <TypeRef>PolygonCullMode::None</TypeRef> by default.
    </Paragraph>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[void SetPolygonCullMode(PolygonCullMode cullMode);]]></Code>
    <SubSection Title="Argument list">
      <ArgumentList>
        <ArgumentListEntry Type="PolygonCullMode!cobalt.graphics.IStateGroupNode.PolygonCullMode" Name="cullMode">
          The polygon cull mode to use
        </ArgumentListEntry>
      </ArgumentList>
    </SubSection>
  </Section>
